Package: TuneBoostTreeBayesian
Title: Bayesian Tuning for Binary Boosted Tree Models
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Joao B. G. de", "Brito", email = "JoaoSabby@users.noreply.github.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides performance-oriented Bayesian hyperparameter tuning for binary boosted tree models with LightGBM as the default engine, XGBoost as a required alternative engine, rBayesianOptimization as the default optimizer, cached stratified cross-validation, warm starts, early stopping, an optional Limbo ask/tell optimizer bridge, a package-native Gaussian-process optimizer fallback, and optional C, Fortran, Rfast, or base R PR-AUC scoring backends.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
